How to run

First,
bundle install

Then,
create a file called 'config.rb' with your Twitter API credentials like so:

Twitter.configure do |config|
  config.consumer_key = 'CONSUMER_KEY'
  config.consumer_secret = 'SECRET'
  config.oauth_token = 'OAUTH_TOKEN'
  config.oauth_token_secret = 'MORE_SECRET'
end


then cd into the directory

ruby ./social_profile.rb <twitterhandle>